comment.text: The translation key "Left menu" is used to describe a left navigation menu element. It appears as a label in the PortalSettings page and will be displayed in English translations, indicating that this is where the user can access developer tools and other settings.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Arabic translation "القائمة المتبقية" (Al-Qa'ima al-Mutabaqiyya) translates to "remaining menu" which doesn't accurately convey the meaning of "Left menu." It implies a menu that is left over, rather than a menu located on the left side.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: القائمة الجانبية (Al-Qa'ima al-Janibiyya) - This translates to "Side Menu" and is a more accurate representation of a left-hand menu. Alternatively, القائمة اليسرى (Al-Qa'ima al-Yusra) - "Left Menu" is a direct translation and might be appropriate depending on the context.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Menü' is too literal and doesn't fully convey the meaning of 'Left menu'. While 'Menü' is the general word for 'menu', it lacks the 'left' specificity.

While "Ցանկ" (Tsank') can mean 'list' or 'menu', it's a somewhat literal translation of 'menu'. A more natural Armenian translation for 'Left menu' might be something like 'Ձախ ցանկ' (Dzhakh tsank) - 'Left list/menu'.
The Lao translation "ເມນູ" is simply the transliteration of the English word "menu". It doesn't convey the meaning of "Left menu". A more accurate translation would describe the menu's position.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ເມນູດ້ານຊ້າຍ

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Dutch translation "Menu links" doesn't accurately reflect the meaning of "Left menu". It describes a list of links rather than the menu itself.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider "Linkermenu" or "Zijmenu" which more closely translates to "Left menu".

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "Menu po lewej" is understandable, a more natural and accurate translation of "Left menu" in Polish would be "Lewe menu". "Menu po lewej" implies a menu *on* the left, rather than *being* the left menu.
The translation "Meniu" is too literal and doesn't accurately convey the meaning of "Left menu". It simply means "Menu".

The translation "වමේ වට්ටෝරුව" (vame vattoruwa) literally translates to 'left plate' or 'left tray'. 'Left menu' should convey the concept of a sidebar or navigation menu on the left side of a screen.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: වමේ මෙනු (vame menu) - Using the English word 'menu' transliterated into Sinhala is a common and understandable approach. Alternatively, consider 'බැල් Anlage' (bael anlaege) which translates to 'left panel' or 'left sidebar', depending on the specific context.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While technically a direct translation, "Леви мени" doesn't sound natural in Serbian. The preferred phrasing would be "Леви менији" to match the English pluralization (menus) or "Лева мени листа" for a clearer, more descriptive term, meaning 'Left menu list'.

While 'Menu trái' is technically 'left menu,' a more natural and common Vietnamese translation for 'Left menu' in a UI context would be 'Menu bên trái' or simply 'Menu trái'. 'Menu trái' can be ambiguous and might be interpreted as 'left menu item' instead of the entire left menu.
